> What exactly is GIT? 
--Git is known as the most popular version control system(VCS).

> What is Version Control System ?
--Version Control is a software that tracks and manages changes to files over time. 
  Version Control System allow users to revisit earlier versions of files, compare changes between versions of files, undo changes and a lot more. 

> Other Version Control System ?
--Git is just one of the many VCS. 
  The other VCS have the same goal, but varies in the process of work. 
  Other VCS includes -> Subversion, CVS, Mercuruial.

> Uses of GIT?
-- a> Track changes across  multiple files. 
   b> Compare versions of a project.
   c> "Time Travel" back to old versions. 
   d>  Revert to a previous version. 
   e> Collaborate and share changes. 
   f> Combine changes. 

> Who uses GIT?
-- a> Developers - It is a must have skill for developers. 
   b> Non- Developers -They learn git to collaborate with other co-workers. 
   c> Governments - Nowadays, Government also uses git. 
   d> Scientists - Commonly used by research teams for storing data and manage. 
   e> Writers - Some writers use git to manage drafts and writings. 
            Anyone can use GIT to store their data and manage it over time. 

> GIT vs GITHUB.
-- GIT != GITHUB [!= -> Not equal to] 
   GIT - It runs locally on our machine. 
         We don't need Github to use GIT. 
         No need of internet. 
         No need to sign up for an account.

   GITHUB - It is a service that hosts git repositories in the cloud. 
            It makes it easier to collaboate with other people. 
            Do need to sign up for an account. 
            It's an online place to share work that is done using GIT. 

